  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study aims to propose a perioperative comprehensive intervention based on health
      behavior model to improve cardiopulmonary function and quality of life among lung cancer
      patients following
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This study aims to propose a perioperative comprehensive intervention based on health
      behavior model to improve cardiopulmonary function and quality of life among lung cancer
      patients following:

        1. understanding multi-dimensional factors affecting cardiopulmonary function and quality
           of life

        2. development of multidisciplinary comprehensive intervention

        3. evaluation the effects of comprehensive intervention using cluster design
    </textblock>
